-----------
Accessories
-----------
    * Arduino Mega 2560 Board X1
    * USB cable type A/B X1
    * 3.5" TFT LCD 480x320 HD color screen module for Arduino UNO & MEGA 2560
        board with touch panel X1
    * Dual axis XY Joystick with push switch for Arduino X1
    * Breadboard X1
    * Male jumper wire X7
    * Male-to-female jumper wire X5

--------------------
Wiring Instructions
--------------------
    * Arduino Analog Pin A8 <--> BB <--> Joystick VRy
    * Arduino Analog Pin A9 <--> BB <--> Joystick VRx
    * Arduino Digital pin 53 <--> BB <--> Joystick Pin SW
    * Arduino GND <--> BB GND <--> BB GND <--> Joystick GND
    * Arduino +5V Pin <--> BB +5V <--> BB +5V <--> Joystick +5V

---------------------
Running Instructions
---------------------
    1. Connect the Arduino with the appropriate componenets (ex: TFT display) to
    a computer using an A-B style USB cable. Ensure that the Arduino is using
    the proper serial port (/dev/ttyACMO0).

    2. In the directory containing the files a1part2.cpp and Makefile, use
    the command "make upload" to upload the code to the Arduino.

-----
Notes
-----
    * a1part2.cpp is the main program.
    * Helper files:
        * lcd_image - routine for drawing an image patch from the SD card to the
            LCD display.
        * yeg_draw - implements map redrawing and helper functions.
        * yeg_rest_coords - converts between x and y positions on the YEG map to
            latitude and longitude, and vice versa.
        * yeg_sort - implements of insertion sort and quicksort along with
            helper functions.
